ngshmmalign
------------------------------------------
ngshmmalign is a profile HMM aligner for NGS reads designed particularly for
small genomes (such as those of RNA viruses like HIV-1 and HCV) that
experience substantial biological insertions and deletions.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.10-1
  libboost_filesystem1.66-1.66.0-1
  libboost_iostreams1.66-1.66.0-1
  libboost_program_options1.66-1.66.0-1
  libboost_system1.66-1.66.0-1
  libgcc1-14.4.0-1
  libgomp1-14.4.0-1
  libstdc++6-14.4.0-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-15-3
  autoconf-archive-2024.10.16-1
  automake-20250528-1
  binutils-2.46.1-1
  cygport-0.37.7-1
  gcc-core-14.4.0-1
  gcc-g++-14.4.0-1
  libboost-devel-1.66.0-1
  make-4.4.1-2

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/cbg-ethz/ngshmmalign

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/cbg-ethz/ngshmmalign/archive/refs/tags/0.1.1.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack ngshmmalign-0.1.1-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./ngshmmalign-0.1.1-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/ngshmmalign-0.1.1-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/ngshmmalign-0.1.1-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(ngshmmalign)
  /usr/bin/ngshmmalign.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/ngshmmalign.README
  /usr/share/doc/ngshmmalign/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/ngshmmalign/README.md

